I’m deeply honored and incredibly humbled to see my article featured in Forbes India Magazine. It’s an extraordinary moment that fills me with gratitude. 

A heartfelt thank you to Forbes India for acknowledging my efforts and contributions to the Indian tattoo industry.

Three years ago, I penned in my journal a vision of being recognized in Forbes magazine for my work in the tattoo realm. Today, that vision has turned into reality, a powerful testament to the power of manifestation. 

@forbesindia @alienstattooindia @alienstattooschool @sunnybhanushali

Some tattoos aren’t designed.
They’re received.

When Gaurav walked in with a feeling he couldn’t explain, Sunny didn’t start with sketches he started with poem that read his soul. What followed wasn’t just a design process. It was something divine.

From Shiva’s gaze to the devotee’s surrender every line in this tattoo came through presence, not planning.

The final result transcended from being a mere tattoo to a mirror of everything he had quietly become.

If you carry a sacred story too, one that keeps whispering maybe it’s time to honour it in ink.
Comment “Awakened” or DM us.

latestPosts.caption:
I believe that the universe(God) is always trying to communicate with you through everything around you, it speaks to you through people, nature, sound, everything you can possibly experience. It is always guiding you to be the best of you(self)

But for each individual, there is one channel of communication which resonates more than others, for some it is mantras, mentors, parents, instincts and hunches, videos, music, lyrics and more. 

For me, it is books, I believe that God(universe) speaks to me through books, or I rather resonate more with it. All my life I have been guided through the scriptures and books I have read. Whenever I need answers I pick up a random book and start reading from anywhere and I end up getting an answers.

The most difficult times and hurdles I have had, I found answers in the books. The more I read, the more clearly I hear the universe. 

I have risen from the slums, the lowest economical region of India to what I am today, and I can full heartedly vouch for the fact that, books have played a major role in my success story. 

P.S. I am not into reading religious and spiritual books as such, however I have read Bhagavad-Gita, Bible and Quran, to understand the science of religion.

latestPosts.caption:
Some initiatives are not planned, but they are felt.

Cause for the Paws is one of those. It’s a movement born out of love for the voiceless, the wagging tails and the eyes that say everything without a word.

Who better to walk you through this journey other than Sunny Bhanushali (@sunnybhanushali), the heart behind it all.

Join with us for the cause that’s more than just an event, it’s a tribute to the healing, hope and the joy our furry friends bring into our lives.

I remember when I was a kid, living in slums, getting to see a luxury car was a special thing for us. In my school days I started collecting hot wheels(used ones), the favourite one was always a BMW. I use to play/visualise myself driving these different beasts on the wild roads. 

When I got out of college, started my first job as a sweeper, 700 Rs a month salary, I use to tell my grandma that I will buy BMW one day, she used to call me ‘shaikhchilli’ (the one who fakes big dreams and has nothing in his pockets, only big words). My relatives used to make fun of me too. 

When I started writing a journal, I remember first thing I wrote was a manifestation note, which had a BMW car in it. Later I built vision boards and believed in manifestations, while everyone around me called me a fool.

5 years ago, I bought one, BMW 6GT, limited edition. A huge milestone in my success journey. It’s not about the car, it’s about the journey this car depicts in my life. It became a mark of success, a statement for all the people in my world, positioned me as an inspiration, a black wolf of the family achieved something which no one ever achieved in my entire family (all generations). 

All the words I said and I say now has a weightage, people want to hear me out, they want my guidance and want to know how I did it. It’s like I have cracked the success code. :)

Feels like it’s time for another mark, another milestone :)

Just thought of sharing this, speaking my heart out, no intention of bragging here
